- All documentation is substantial and production-ready
- Component is immediately usable after forge completes

## Success Criteria

After forge completes, the component should have:

✅ All 4 proto files with validations
✅ **Every CEL message is user-facing quality** (clear, actionable, empathetic -- see rule `002-spec-validate`, "VALIDATION MESSAGE QUALITY")
✅ Generated .pb.go stubs
✅ spec_test.go with validation tests
✅ **Component tests execute and pass** (validates buf.validate rules)
✅ Registered in cloud_resource_kind.proto
✅ Complete user-facing documentation (README.md)
✅ Comprehensive research documentation (docs/README.md)
✅ Pulumi module that compiles and works
✅ **Pulumi entrypoint at canonical root** (`iac/pulumi/main.go` is `package main`; no `main/` or `entrypoint/` subdir)
✅ Terraform module that validates and works
✅ **Cross-engine parity gate passed** (Phase 6b) -- Pulumi and Terraform agree on namespace, naming basis, labels, selectors, feature coverage, dependency ordering, and stack outputs; any divergence carries a `PARITY-EXCEPTION:` comment in both modules
✅ Supporting files (manifests, debug scripts, module overviews)
✅ Initial presets generated (2-3 common configuration templates)
✅ Build validation passed -- BOTH `go build ./apis/.../v1/...` AND the release-equivalent `go build -o /dev/null ./apis/.../v1/iac/pulumi`
✅ Component test validation passed (`go test -v ./apis/.../v1/`)

**Result:** A production-ready deployment component matching 95-100% of ideal state with all tests passing!